      • getAttachmentByFileId

        public File getAttachmentByFileId(String userId,
                                  String fileId)
        Retrieves a previously uploaded attachment to an entry by it's unique file identifier This file identifier is assigned on upload
        Returns:
        Attachment file if one is found with the identifier, null otherwise (including if the user making the request does not have read permissions on the entry that this attachment is associated with)

      • save

        public Attachment save(Account account,
                       Attachment attachment,
                       InputStream inputStream)
        Save attachment to the database and the disk. Entry has to be a transferred entry (Visibility of 2) or the account must have write permissions to it
        Parameters:
        account - account for user making request. Can be null if method is called as a result of a transfer
        attachment - attachment
        inputStream - The data stream of the file.
        Returns:
        Saved attachment.
